Package com.linkedin.alpini.base.cache

Class PhantomHashCache<K,​V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.linkedin.alpini.base.cache.PhantomHashCache<K,​V>
  • public final class PhantomHashCache<K,​V>
extends java.lang.Object
    A cache backed which uses PhantomReferences to cache instances of values to avoid multiple instances of the same cached object. This cache should not prevent a Value object from being garbage collected. The purpose of this map is to ensure that there is little penalty in storing objects for a short period of time. Objects stored within the map are assumed to be immutable. The clone function provided to the constructor should return a lightweight clone of the supplied object which references the same objects within it. As long as the keys are unique, it is possible to use multiple backing stores with only one PhantomHashCache providing a cache.

        Creates a new, empty phantom map with an initial table size based on the given number of elements (initialCapacity), table density (loadFactor), and number of concurrently updating threads (concurrencyLevel).
        Parameters:
        clone - lightweight clone function
        initialCapacity - the initial capacity. The implementation performs internal sizing to accommodate this many elements, given the specified load factor.
        loadFactor - the load factor (table density) for establishing the initial table size
        concurrencyLevel - the estimated number of concurrently updating threads. The implementation may use this value as a sizing hint.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the initial capacity is negative or the load factor or concurrencyLevel are nonpositive

        Associates the specified value with the specified key in this map If the map previously contained a mapping for the key, the new value is ignored. If the map did not previously contain a mapping for the key, the new value is stored within the backing store and a PhantomReference is made to it.
        Parameters:
        key - key with which the specified value is to be associated
        store - backing store which the supplied key/value should be persisted within.
        value - value to be associated with the specified key
